        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 53,
      "author": {
        "id": 1087048
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-02-12T17:20:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is just to make it easier for methods that return this to indicate success. It hides any knowledge of what a successful error code might be, so whoever uses it doesn\u0027t have to know to use SystemResult::fromErrno(0) to indicate success. I also think it\u0027s more obvious what\u0027s going on when reading \"return SystemResult::kSuccess;\"",
      "parentUuid": "1ddb703a_23ad6e67",
